title: Channing Tatum sends shout out video for Summerville High homecoming game
text:
Channing Tatum sends shout out video for Summerville High homeco - WCIV-TV | ABC News 4 - Charleston News, Sports, Weather Member Center: Channing Tatum sends shout out video for Summerville High homecoming game Posted: Updated: 
SUMMERVILLE, S.C. (WCIV) -- Summerville High School has some star power heading into its homecoming game against Ashley Ridge. 
Channing Tatum gave the school a shout out in a video posted to Facebook by the school. 
"You, what's up Summerville High? Channing here. I'm just keeping y'all in my thoughts, OK. Y'all be good and tear up homecoming. Go Green Wave," he said. 
The video was posted about noon Thursday and has more than 3,300 shares in the 12 hours since it was posted. 
The Green Wave plays Ashley Ridge in their homecoming matchup -- once Lowcountry schools can get back to school and get a series of games rescheduled that were missed after historic flooding and record rainfall in the area. Most Popular
